events.name: Study Jams - UET Peshawar
events.description:
Many people learn better when they learn in groups. Web Study Jams is a GDG Islamabad community-run study group for developers covering mobile web design and development. This current study jam will be about Mobile Site Certification. The Study Jams objective is to raise the technical proficiency of global community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

Mobile Site Certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate understanding in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

How long does it take: Approximately 3-4 hours of study material, followed by 90 minute (multiple choice) exam

End Result: Students that complete the exam receive a printable certificate to verify status as a certified mobile sites professional and a Google Partners public profile page listing the certification.

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, applications deployment.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam 2019 - COMSATS Islamabad
events.description:
Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers. This is a great opportunity to bring members of the community together to learn something in person. These training will give the community members a specific skill they can use for personal development or career advancement.

With a Cloud Study Jam, you will learn the fundamental tools and capabilities of Google Cloud. Attendees will receive free access to our online labs. You can choose any of our recommended tracks to run with the community: Machine Learning, Kubernetes, Certification, IoT, and Security.

After the session, attendees can continue taking labs to earn Google Cloud badges.

==============================================

Cloud Study Jams 2019 Islamabad Topics:
►Introduction to Qwiklabs
►Setting up virtual machine or window environment
►Intro to cloud shell and google cloud
►Hello node kubernetes
►Stack driver: Qwikstart
►Setting up network and HTTP Loaders
►Provision services with GCP marketplace
►Creating a persistent disk
Note:
No eligibility criterion is required.Anyone willing to learn more about the topics mentioned above ca join the session.

Timing: 11:30 am - 1:30 pm | 2 hours
Venue: COMSATS Islamabad

events.description:

Dr. Maria Riaz is a Sr. Software Engineer at Google. She has 12+ years of research and academics experience in the field of software engineering, security and privacy. She has taught undergraduate students in the field of computer science (at GIKI and NUST) before switching to industry after completing her Ph.D. She enjoys solving problems, bringing people together and getting things done. She has taught hundreds of students and feels inspired to create impact beyond herself through teaching, mentoring and building a community of passionate and driven individuals.

events.description:
GDG Islamabad and GCDC Islamabad have collaborated with a Googler to bring you a super cool workshop on Big Data and Google Cloud Platform!

Yes, you heard that right! Usman Ali, Big Data Product Specialist at Google Norway, is flying to Pakistan to deliver this hands-on workshop.

Big Data Workshop [Participation Cost - PKR 500] (2 PM - 5 PM)
► Registrations (15-20 mins)
► Introduction to GCP and its products (20 mins)
► Machine Learning & AI (with a demo/lab on TF via Notebook AI) (60mins)
► Big Data (with a demo on BigQuery and BigQuery ML) (35mins)
► Snacks break (15 mins)

Fireside Chat With Usman Ali [No Participation Cost] [5 PM - 6 PM]
► Fireside chat (30-40 mins)
► Networking (20-30 mins)

Please note that the workshop (from 2 PM to 5 PM) has a participation cost of PKR 500 while the fireside chat (from 5 PM to 6 PM) is free.

Due to limited seating, the slots for both the sessions will be allotted on first come first-served basis. Payment details for the workshop will be shared over email with the shortlisted candidates.

Moreover, registrations are mandatory for both sessions. GDG Islamabad team will evaluate your responses and IF you are shortlisted, you will get the confirmation email. Anyone who has not received an email invite from our team would not be allowed inside the venue.

Limited seating so register now at: http://bit.ly/2JDrIAF
Fb Event: https://web.facebook.com/events/730137157423050/

events.name: Fireside Chat with Usman Ali - Googler
events.description:
Fireside Chat with Usman Ali - Big Data Product Specialist from Google Norway.

Usman has over 13 years of industry experience in Big Data and Analytics domain. He is part of Google Cloud’s Big Data Product Specialist team in Northern Europe to help large Enterprises move to the Cloud. Before Google, he has worked with Teradata for 10 years on Data Warehouse, BI, CRM and other technologies typical to DWH environment.

He is originally from Pakistan, graduated from FAST Islamabad, however, he has lived and worked in Norway from the past 10 years. Besides work, he loves spending time with his family, playing squash, binge on Netflix and go on road-trips.

Flutter is Google’s UI toolkit for building beautiful, natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop from a single codebase.

What will you learn from this event?
1. Making a fresh start flutter app
2. Extending the fresh made app to multi screen mobile app
3. Adding some widgets (UI components) on screens
4. Navigation between screens in a multi screen flutter while interacting with widgets
5. Running flutter app on Android and iOS emulator/simulator

https://tinyurl.com/FlutterViewingParty

events.description:
Team #GDGIslamabad is thrilled to bring you an amazing live session on Chrome DevTools.
The Chrome DevTools feature provides an amazing set of tools built directly into the Google Chrome browser. From remote debugging to editing pages on-the-fly & building websites, faster, there’s a whole range of interesting features worth digging up in Chrome, and we’re going to look them up in this session with Arslan Khattak - Junior Front end Web Developer & Co-Founder of MSP Islamabad.
======================
Session outline:
- Introducing the host, learning objectives and setting the agenda for the workshop
- A general overview of chrome dev tools, What is it? Why should we use it?
- Deep dive into elements tab
- Learning how to change HTML structure in the chrome dev tools
- Playing around with CSS
- Debugging basic web page to fix bugs
- Exercise to practice what we have covered so far
- Using Chrome dev tools as an editor
- Getting familiar with the network tab and its various features
- Q&A
- Wrapping up
=======================

#GDGIslamabad #StayHome #StaySafe
